race.comment: EMERALD SPRINTER (1) drifted back settling but did best work late to finish 5th at this track over 342m (20.23). Form here at the trip sound including six wins. The form from his last run stacks up well. Tough to beat if on-song. BONNIE DIVA (5) carved over from wide out and boxed on strongly to finish 0.8 lengths away in second (20.03) behind Slipper's Solo at this track. Winning chance. SHEA'S ENTITY (2) showed little early speed at his last couple, the latest finishing sixth (20.26) in a Grade 5 at this track. Strong form has emerged from his last run. Has ability and a bold showing is expected. SMOOTH VIXEN (8) jumped best and was never headed last time. Hard to beat.
